# Generics — what and why

## `<E>` is a type parameter

- Filled in per use site: `List<String>`, `Map<String, Integer>`

## Two wins

- **Compile-time type safety** — no `Integer` into a `List<String>`
- **No casts** — `get(0)` already returns `String`

```java
List rawList = new ArrayList();
String s = (String) rawList.get(1);   // ClassCastException at runtime
List<String> safe = ...; safe.get(0); // no cast
```
